   "source": [
    "# Chat Agent with Context Management - Llama 3.2-1B\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates a bare-bones chat agent using Llama 3.2-1B-Instruct with advanced context management features.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Features\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Fixed Window Context Management**: Keep only the last N messages to prevent context overflow\n",
    "- **History Toggle**: Compare agent performance with and without conversation history\n",
    "- **HF Token Authentication**: Load from .env file or enter manually with secure prompt\n",
    "- **Interactive Interface**: Single-turn and continuous chat modes\n",
    "- **Helper Functions**: Reset conversation, view history, and more\n",
    "\n",
    "## How It Works\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Chat history is maintained as plain text (list of dictionaries)\n",
    "2. For each turn, the entire history is tokenized and fed to the model\n",
    "3. Fixed Window keeps only recent messages to manage context size\n",
    "4. Model generates response based on conversation context\n",
    "\n",
    "## Authentication\n",
    "\n",
    "The notebook will:\n",
    "1. First try to load HF_TOKEN from .env file\n",
    "2. If not found, prompt you to enter your token manually (input hidden)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Usage\n",
    "\n",
    "Run cells 1-8 in order to set up the chat agent, then use Cell 10 for interactive chatting!"
   ]
  },
