    "## How to Use This Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "### Single-Turn Chat (Recommended)\n",
    "\n",
    "Modify the message in Cell 10 and re-run it to chat:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "user_message = \"What's the weather like?\"\n",
    "response = chat(user_message)\n",
    "print(f\"You: {user_message}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Assistant: {response}\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**For multi-turn conversations**: Simply edit the message in Cell 10 and run it multiple times. The agent will remember your conversation (if history is enabled).\n",
    "\n",
    "### Helper Functions\n",
    "\n",
    "Run these in any cell to manage your conversation:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Reset conversation**: `reset_conversation()` - Clears chat history and starts fresh\n",
    "- **View history**: `show_history()` - Display all messages in the current conversation\n",
    "\n",
    "### Testing Context Management\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Test Fixed Window**: Set `MAX_MESSAGES = 6` in Cell 3, re-run cells 6-8, have 10+ turn conversation using Cell 10, run `show_history()` to verify only 6 messages kept\n",
    "2. **Test No History**: Set `ENABLE_HISTORY = False` in Cell 3, re-run cells 6-8, verify agent doesn't remember previous turns\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why Not a While Loop?\n",
    "\n",
    "The `input()` function in while loops doesn't work reliably in Jupyter notebooks (especially JupyterLab and VS Code). The recommended approach is to edit and re-run Cell 10 for each message, which is actually more convenient for testing and experimentation!"
   ]
